claims:
Claims 1. At least one device comprising: one or more processors; and memory storing modules that, when executed by the one or more processors, cause the at least one device to perform operations comprising: receiving a data set including a real number, the real number including an integer portion and a fractional portion; and encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in a polynomial, the fractional portion of the real number represented as at least one top coefficient of the polynomial, wherein the at least one top coefficient is determined by a length of the polynomial determined for at least one homomorphic operation, wherein the real number is encoded in the polynomial as a single polynomial without converting the real number to an integer, and wherein the encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in the polynomial reduces a processing time of the one or more processors when performing the at least one homomorphic operation. 2. The at least one device of claim 1, wherein the operations further comprise: generating an expanded polynomial representing the real number using base two, the expanded polynomial including at least one coefficient raised to a negative power; wrapping around the at least one coefficient raised to the negative power as the at least one top coefficient of the polynomial; and negating the at least one top coefficient of the polynomial. 3. A computer-implemented method for performing encoding for homomorphic encryption by at least one processor, the method comprising: receiving a data set including a real number, the real number including an integer portion and a fractional portion; and encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in a polynomial, the fractional portion of the real number represented as at least one top coefficient of the polynomial, wherein the at least one top coefficient is determined by a length of the polynomial determined for at least one homomorphic operation, wherein the real number is encoded in the polynomial as a single polynomial without converting the real number to an integer, and 

 wherein the encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in the polynomial reduces a processing time of the at least one processor when performing the at least one homomorphic operation. 4. The method of claim 3, further comprising: encrypting the polynomial as a ciphertext; transmitting the ciphertext via a network to a server; and receiving, from the server, a result of a performance of the at least one homomorphic operation on the ciphertext. 5. The method of any one of claims 3 or 4, wherein the at least one homomorphic operation includes at least one of addition, subtraction, multiplication, or division. 6. The method of any one of claims 3 through 5, wherein the encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in the polynomial further includes: generating an expanded polynomial representing the real number using base two, the expanded polynomial including at least one coefficient raised to a negative power; and wrapping around the at least one coefficient raised to the negative power as the at least one top coefficient of the polynomial. 7. The method of claim 6, wherein the wrapping around the at least one coefficient further includes negating the at least one top coefficient of the polynomial. 8. The method of any one of claims 3 through 7, further comprising: determining that the real number can be approximated as an approximate real number; and determining a fractional base to encode the polynomial, the fractional base based at least partly on the approximate real number. 9. The method of any one of claims 3 through 8, further comprising applying a slot encoding to the polynomial to generate a slot-encoded polynomial to increase a number of homomorphic operations that can be performed on the slot-encoded polynomial. 10. A system comprising: one or more processors; and memory storing modules that, when executed by the one or more processors, cause the system to perform operations comprising: receiving a data set including a real number, the real number including an integer portion and a fractional portion; 

 encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in a polynomial, the fractional portion of the real number represented as at least one top coefficient of the polynomial, wherein the at least one top coefficient is determined by a length of the polynomial determined for at least one homomorphic operation, wherein the real number is encoded in the polynomial as a single polynomial without converting the real number to an integer, and wherein the encoding the integer portion and the fractional portion in the polynomial reduces a processing time of the one or more processors when performing at least one homomorphic operation. 11. The system of claim 10, wherein the operations further comprise: encrypting the polynomial as a ciphertext; transmitting the ciphertext via a network to a server; and receiving, from the server, a result of a performance of the at least one homomorphic operation on the ciphertext. 12. The system of claims 10 or 11, wherein the at least one homomorphic operation includes at least one of addition, subtraction, multiplication, or division. 13. The system of any one of claims 10 through 12, wherein the operations further comprise: generating an expanded polynomial representing the real number using base two, the expanded polynomial including at least one coefficient raised to a negative power; and wrapping around the at least one coefficient raised to the negative power as the at least one top coefficient of the polynomial. 14. The system of claim 13, wherein the wrapping around the at least one coefficient further includes negating the at least one top coefficient of the polynomial. 15. The system of any one of claims 10 through 14, further comprising: determining that the real number can be approximated as an approximate real number; and determining a fractional base to encode the polynomial, the fractional base based at least partly on the approximate real number.
